---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — LurraGrid"
  description="LurraGrid's mission, mythology, and approach to underground pumped hydro power for AI compute."
>
  <Nav />

  <!-- Hero — full bleed tunnel image -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[75vh] flex flex-col justify-end overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/about-hero.jpg"
        alt="LurraCore underground tunnel infrastructure"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover object-center hero-drift"
      />
      <!-- Top fade protects nav -->
      <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,0,0,0.92) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.40) 20%, transparent 50%);"></div>
      <!-- Bottom fade lifts text -->
      <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.97) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.60) 35%, transparent 60%);"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="relative px-6 md:px-12 pt-28 md:pt-48 pb-12 md:pb-24 max-w-5xl mx-auto w-full flex flex-col justify-center min-h-[60vh] md:min-h-[75vh]">
      <p class="font-body text-xs tracking-[0.3em] uppercase mb-6 animate-fade-up eyebrow-over-image">About</p>
      <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-7xl text-frost leading-none mb-6 animate-fade-up-delay-1">
        POWERING THE AI ERA<br /><span style="color:#FF6600;">FROM THE GROUND DOWN.</span>
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="border-t border-rule mx-8 md:mx-12"></div>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="py-24 px-8 md:px-12 reveal border-b border-rule section-blue-deep w-full">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-8">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <p class="font-body text-xs tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-royal mt-2">What We Are</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-7">
        <p class="font-body text-xl text-frost leading-relaxed mb-6">
          LurraGrid is an infrastructure firm. We convert abandoned hard rock mines into LurraCore underground pumped hydro power plants and deliver firm, dispatchable behind-the-meter power to AI data centers under 20-year take-or-pay Power Delivery Agreements.
        </p>
        <p class="font-body text-base text-frost-dim leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The AI era demands power at a scale and speed the grid cannot provide. Interconnection queues run five to seven years. Permitting for new generation stretches longer. ESG mandates restrict gas. The result is a structural supply gap between where the compute wants to go and where the power can reach it.
        </p>
        <p class="font-body text-base text-frost-dim leading-relaxed">
          LurraGrid closes that gap. We are not building new infrastructure — we are commissioning infrastructure that already exists, at depth, in proven hard rock formations, across the United States. The mines are built. The shafts are sunk. The geology is validated. We convert them into power plants.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Model -->
  <section class="py-24 px-8 md:px-12 reveal border-b border-rule section-blue-mid w-full">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-8">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <p class="font-body text-xs tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-royal mt-2">The Model</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-7">
        <p class="font-body text-base text-frost-dim leading-relaxed mb-6">
          LurraGrid is an energy arbitrage platform. We acquire curtailed renewable energy at near-zero or negative cost during overnight off-peak windows — energy that wind and nuclear operators generate but the grid cannot absorb. We store it as potential hydraulic head in underground reservoirs. We dispatch it as firm, schedulable power during daytime premium hours.
        </p>
        <p class="font-body text-base text-frost-dim leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The data center operator receives power directly behind the meter — no grid interconnection queue, no transmission costs, no fuel exposure. LurraGrid holds the spread between curtailed input and firm output. That spread is the business.
        </p>
        <p class="font-body text-base text-frost-dim leading-relaxed">
          The LurraPDA — Power Delivery Agreement — is a 20-year take-or-pay contract. Infrastructure-grade duration. Infrastructure-grade contract structure. Infrastructure-grade returns.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Underground -->
  <section class="py-24 px-8 md:px-12 reveal border-b border-rule section-orange-accent w-full">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-8">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <p class="font-body text-xs tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-royal mt-2">Why Underground</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-7">
        <p class="font-body text-base text-frost-dim leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Surface pumped hydro requires two lakes, a mountain, and a decade of permitting. Underground pumped hydro requires a mine. The United States has thousands of abandoned hard rock mines with existing shafts, proven geology, and clear ownership — mostly municipal or federal. The civil engineering is already done.
        </p>
        <p class="font-body text-base text-frost-dim leading-relaxed">
          LurraAtlas has pre-screened 950 sites across 15 states. Our first three — Mather B in Michigan, Quincy in Michigan, and Comstock in Nevada — represent three different ore types, three different depth profiles, and three different demand corridors. That is the portfolio.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mythology -->
  <section class="pt-32 pb-0 px-8 md:px-12 reveal section-cta w-full">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="font-body text-xs tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-royal mb-8">The Name</p>
      <p class="font-display font-bold text-5xl md:text-7xl text-frost mb-12">LURRA</p>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-frost-dim leading-relaxed italic">
        Lurra — earth goddess of the Basque people — lives underground in the caves. She holds amazing treasures in her bosom.
      </p>
      <div class="w-16 h-px bg-royal mx-auto mt-12"></div>
      <p class="font-body text-sm text-frost-dim mt-8 leading-relaxed">
        The mines were dug for what was below. We return to them for what they can hold. The treasure now is energy — stored at depth, dispatched on demand, delivered to the machines that run the age we are building.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-8 md:px-12 text-center reveal">
    <a
      href="/contact"
      class="inline-block font-display font-bold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase px-10 py-4 bg-royal text-frost hover:bg-royal-light transition-colors duration-300"
    >
      Partner With LurraGrid →
    </a>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Base>
